DATA CLOUD
Calculated Insights Processing and Retention Times

The processing and retention times for a calculated insight depend on the amount of data in the underlying data model objects (DMOs) and the time dimensions used in Data Cloud. Keep your calculated insights up to date when data changes by using the schedule feature. You can specify the frequency, start date, and time to process a calculated insight. You can process a calculated insight every 6, 12, or 24 hours, or process it manually. However, if a calculated insight is created before the availability of the schedule feature, it runs on the previous system schedule and is processed four times a day.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Edition
Retention Periods

Metrics retention in a calculated insight is based on the date and time dimension in the GROUP BY statement. For example, a calculated insight can have only 48 hours of data per hour resolution at any time. Data that’s older than 48 hours isn’t retained. This rule applies only if you’re using Data Cloud functions, such as CdpHour, CdpDay, CdpMonth, CdpQuarter, and CdpYear.

METRICS TIME GRANULARITY	EXAMPLE	RETENTION PERIOD
Hourly	Hourly transactions by store	48 hours
Daily	Daily product sold by product category	365 days
Monthly	Total monthly visits by the customer	5 years
Quarterly	Quarterly sales	5 years
Yearly	Total yearly spend by the customer	20 years
Calculated Insights Rollup Behavior

Because the metrics retention period is shorter at a higher time dimension resolution, the system rolls up the data to the next tier time dimension. Use the rolled-up time dimension while retrieving the data or specifying a time-based query in segmentation.

DATA GRANULARITY	ROLLUP INTERVAL	ROLLED UP TO
Hourly	24 hours	Daily
Daily	30 days	Monthly
Monthly	3 months	Quarterly
Quarterly	4 quarters	Yearly

Only calculated insights with these aggregate functions are rolled up:

Sum
Min
Max
Count
Avg
Mean
Guidelines and Limits
FUNCTION	LIMIT	DESCRIPTION
Total number of calculated insight batch runs per year, per tenant	100,000	The number of times an insight has been refreshed over a period of 365 days.
Maximum calculated insight execution time	2 hours	The maximum amount of time that the insight runs before it’s terminated.

For guidance on limits, see Data Cloud Limits and Guidelines.
